Reference guide for shadcn/ui components used throughout the project. These components are copy-paste ready and work with all component libraries.

## Overview

This project uses shadcn/ui components from the **October 2025 release**, which introduced several new components specifically designed for common UI patterns:

- **InputGroup**: Input with icons, buttons, labels and more
- **Spinner**: Loading state indicator
- **Kbd**: Display keyboard keys
- **ButtonGroup**: Group related buttons together
- **Field**: Complete form field abstraction
- **Item**: Flexible container for lists and cards
- **Empty**: Empty state displays

See [shadcn/ui Changelog](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/changelog) for full details.

## InputGroup

Input with icons, buttons, and addons. Perfect for search inputs, filters, and complex form controls.

### Installation

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add input-group
```

### Basic Usage

```tsx
import {
  InputGroup,
  InputGroupAddon,
  InputGroupButton,
  InputGroupInput,
  InputGroupText,
} from "@/components/ui/input-group";
import { Search } from "lucide-react";

<InputGroup>
  <InputGroupAddon align="inline-start">
    <InputGroupText>
      <Search />
    </InputGroupText>
  </InputGroupAddon>
  <InputGroupInput placeholder="Search..." />
</InputGroup>;
```

### With Clear Button

```tsx
import { X } from "lucide-react";

<InputGroup>
  <InputGroupInput
    value={value}
    onChange={(e) => setValue(e.target.value)}
    placeholder="Search..."
  />
  {value && (
    <InputGroupAddon align="inline-end">
      <InputGroupButton
        type="button"
        variant="ghost"
        size="icon-xs"
        onClick={() => setValue("")}
        aria-label="Clear"
      >
        <X />
      </InputGroupButton>
    </InputGroupAddon>
  )}
</InputGroup>;
```

### With Loading Spinner

```tsx
import { Spinner } from "@/components/ui/spinner";

<InputGroup>
  <InputGroupInput placeholder="Search..." />
  {isLoading && (
    <InputGroupAddon align="inline-end">
      <InputGroupText>
        <Spinner />
      </InputGroupText>
    </InputGroupAddon>
  )}
</InputGroup>;
```

### Alignment Options

- `align="inline-start"`: Left side (icons, prefixes)
- `align="inline-end"`: Right side (buttons, suffixes)
- `align="block-start"`: Top (labels, headers)
- `align="block-end"`: Bottom (descriptions, footers)

### Key Points

- `InputGroup` provides unified border/focus states
- Use `InputGroupText` for static content (icons, labels)
- Use `InputGroupButton` for interactive elements
- Always add `aria-label` to icon-only buttons
- Use `type="button"` to prevent form submission

## Spinner

Loading state indicator with customizable size and color.

### Installation

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add spinner
```

### Basic Usage

```tsx
import { Spinner } from "@/components/ui/spinner";

<Spinner />;
```

### In Buttons

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<Button disabled>
  <Spinner />
  Loading...
</Button>;
```

### Custom Size

```tsx
<Spinner className="size-6" />
<Spinner className="size-8" />
```

### Custom Spinner

Replace with your own spinner:

```tsx
import { LoaderIcon } from "lucide-react";
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

function Spinner({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"svg">) {
  return (
    <LoaderIcon
      role="status"
      aria-label="Loading"
      className={cn("size-4 animate-spin", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  );
}
```

### Key Points

- Default size is `size-4` (16px)
- Always includes `role="status"` and `aria-label="Loading"`
- Use in buttons, input groups, or standalone
- Customize with `className` prop

